Basic Qualifications:
 BSEE required (MSEE preferred);
5+ years of experience in the product development industry, specifically with wireless hardware development and verification;
Experience with one or more of the following radio technologies: Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, GPS, cellular;
Proficiency in basic RF concepts;
Proficiency with sophisticated wireless test equipment, specifically Litepoint and/or R&S testers and other typical RF lab equipment (VNA’s, spectrum analyzer, VSG/VSA, etc);
Experience with standard hardware development process, including schematic capture, PCB layout, and RF component characteristic.
Additional Requirements:
 Experience with debug of RF parametric test failures, and identifying root-cause and fixes;
Experience with high-frequency circuit- and system-level simulation tools;
Proven data analysis and reporting skills, including efficient organization and representation of complex test data;
Demonstrated capability of working effectively in a team environment, including taking direction from more senior engineers, working self-sufficiently, and being able to elicit help from team-members when needed;
Ability to learn quickly, and be enthusiastic with a desire to work in a fast-paced but highly rewarding environment;
Strong interpersonal, verbal and written communications skills. 
